  "description": {
    "en": "Master single and multiple inheritance, super(), method resolution order (MRO), and when to use inheritance vs composition.",
    "ta": "ஒற்றை மற்றும் பல பரம்பரை, super(), முறை தீர்மான வரிசை (MRO) ஆகியவற்றில் தேர்ச்சி பெறுங்கள்."
  },
  "xp_reward": 65,
  "story_variants": {
    "en": "## Vaathiyaar's Family Tree\n\nVaathiyaar draws a family tree on the board. \"In every family, children inherit traits from their parents — eye color, height, talent. In Python, classes work the same way!\"\n\n### What is Inheritance?\n- A child class **inherits** all attributes and methods from a parent class\n- The child can **override** methods to customize behavior\n- The child can **extend** with new methods\n\n### Single Inheritance\n\n```python\nclass Animal:\n    def __init__(self, name):\n        self.name = name\n    def speak(self):\n        return 'Some sound'\n\nclass Dog(Animal):  # Dog inherits from Animal\n    def speak(self):\n        return f'{self.name} says Woof!'\n```\n\n### The super() Function\n\n| Concept | Purpose |\n|---------|----------|\n| `super()` | Call a method from the parent class |\n| `super().__init__()` | Initialize parent's attributes |\n| MRO | Method Resolution Order — search path for methods |\n| `isinstance()` | Check if object is instance of a class |\n\n> **Key Concept:** Use `super()` to call the parent's methods instead of hardcoding the parent class name. This makes your code flexible for multiple inheritance."
  },
